body:
What do I love? It's a 1/3 of the price of AirPods, and much cheaper than other brands;
they are comfortable and remain in the ears more easily;
the sound quality is amazing and clear, plus I hardly have to turn up the volume at all to hear the music well in a normal environment;
they really are totally waterproof – I can easily listen to the radio, podcasts or music while showering in the morning!

My only "drawbacks" would be:
you do have to charge them at least daily — but again, this is pretty standard for wireless earphones that use lots of battery, so it's hardly a drawback really;
they don't always pair to each other or connect instantly to your device — I think it usually depends on the strength of whichever device's Bluetooth signal — and sometimes I need to manually open Bluetooth settings on my iPhone to manually connect the earphones. Since these earphones are not an Apple product however, it is understandable that they won't connect as smoothly as AirPods would.

Overall, a happy customer!
